{
  "text": "A 68-year-old man with a history of cardioembolic stroke due to AF at the age of 67 underwent TP for catheter ablation of persistent AF. The patient had undergone total gastrectomy for gastric cancer at the age of 58 and left lower lobectomy for lung cancer at the age of 63. was positioned toward the FO, as previously described. [CITATION_1] However, the needle tip could not reach the posterior region of the FO, which was revealed by intracardiac echocardiography ( Figure 1A ).",
